==English==
===Etymology===
From {{L.}} [[numismatis]], from  Latinised Greek '''numisma''' "coin", from {{Gr.}} '''[[νόμισμα]]''' (''[[nomisma]]'') "current coin, custom", from '''[[νομίζω]]''' (''nomizo'') "to hold or own as a custom, usage, to use customarily, practise, to be used to a thing", hence "to make common use of", from '''[[νόμος]]''' (''nomos'') "usage, custom", from '''[[νέμω]]''' (''nemo'') "to keep, to hold, to watch".

